node.text: Working in restaurants, Lan Lam learned a ton of useful information, including how to open beer with pretty much anything.

node.title: How to Open Beer with Anything 🍺

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 13, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: A triple-decker composition of tubular pasta, spiced meat sauce, and lush béchamel, Greek pastitsio is king among casseroles. Get our recipe for Pastitsio by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 13, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: We love a good brownie that boasts a fudgy, ultra-chocolaty interior. In this version, we add pumpkin for a sweet autumnal dessert. Pumpkin Swirl Brownies recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 13, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: If you want to make the vegetables in your salads a little more exciting, just reach for your peeler and shave them. Read more by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 13, 2021.

node.text: In its simplest, most elegant form, beef stroganoff is a dish of sautéed beef, mushrooms, and onion in a creamy sauce that is typically served over egg noodles. For this streamlined version for two, we opted for tender filet mignon. Get our recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 13, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: For our lobster roll, we mostly adhered to tradition, but we added a hint of crunch in the form of small amounts of lettuce and celery (a contentious addition), and we added complementary brightness with lemon juice, cayenne, and chives. Get our New England Lobster Roll recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 12, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: These mashed potatoes are a staple side for almost any meal. Here’s how we use our slow cooker to ensure evenly cooked potatoes and maximum flavor. Slow-Cooker Classic Mashed Potatoes recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 12, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: Apple fritters should be crisp on the outside and moist within, and their primary flavor should be pure apple. Cast Iron Apple Fritters recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 12, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Here’s how to make baked manicotti, tender pasta tubes stuffed with rich ricotta filling and blanketed with tomato sauce, for two. Recipe link in bio.

node.text: Sure, we like a bowl of creamy polenta, but we think the porridge reaches its full potential when made into fries—perfect for an appetizer or served next to a sandwich or burger. Vegan Polenta Fries with Creamy Chipotle Sauce recipe link in bio.
